description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a full time substantive consultant with an interest in Haemophilia and Thrombosis to join our enthusiastic team and help develop integrated Haematology services for the acute hospitals, community hospitals and primary care in Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role would provide specialist care of patients with inherited bleeding disorders across the Southern Haemophilia Network as well as general non-malignant Haematology laboratory and clinical care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This individual will work as part of a team on 8 consultant haematologists covering Hampshire Hospitals Foundation Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will be primarily based on the Basingstoke and North Hampshire Hospital site but outreach clinics and travel to other hospitals within the Southern Haemophilia Network will be expected.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must be on the GMC register and within 6 months of completion of their CCT at time of interview. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameNoel RymanJob titleClinical LeadEmail addressnoel.ryman@hhft.nhs.ukTelephone number01256 313282Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Sylwia Simpson, Marie Cundall (Transfusion Laboratory Manager) (see below) to make arrangements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secretaries&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Todd and Donna Hodder 01256 313282&lt;/p&gt;
